The paper discusses auction mechanisms and optimization of efficiency and revenue in sponsored search markets, which are topics that fall under game theory (cs.GT), information retrieval (cs.IR), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also analyzes the effects of relevance refinements on the efficiency of the mechanism, which involves data analysis and modeling, falling under data structures (cs.DS) and economics (cs.EC).
